  "observation": "Creative thinking phase: 4 novel cross-disciplinary ideas generated.",
  "suggestion": "REASONING: The core problem: organisms are energy-starved despite food availability. Past 685 cycles show declining fitness. This isn't a morphology problem—it's a COORDINATION problem. Real organisms solve this through (1) temporal synchrony with environment, (2) hierarchical energy budgeting, (3) division of labor. Current SEVO treats foraging as individual random search. What if we apply concepts from oscillatory networks (music/physics), fractal hierarchies (math/biology), and collective behavior (physics/biology/art)?; [Physics (coupled oscillators, resonance)+Music (harmony, entrainment, call-and-response)+Biology (predator-prey synchronization, pheromone waves)] RESONANCE FORAGING: Organisms evolve as coupled oscillators that synchronize with food cluster oscillation patterns. Instead of random search, they emit low-frequency 'scanning pulses' that induce food patches to become temporarily concentrated. Beauty emerges from emergent wave interference patterns. Energy starvation solves because organisms and food phase-lock—food arrives predictably when organisms need it, eliminating wasteful search. — Math: Kuramoto model: dθᵢ/dt = ωᵢ + K∑sin(θⱼ-θᵢ). Food patches become driven oscillators. Beauty is encoded in phase coherence; efficiency emerges from energy stored in synchronized rhythms vs. random motion. — Test: Measure phase-lag between organism movement and food clustering over time. If resonance works, phase lag should decrease (organisms anticipating food). Energy cost per food consumed should drop. Visual beauty should increase (emergent wave patterns visible in organism trails).; [Mathematics (fractals, multi-scale analysis, renormalization)+Developmental Biology (recursive gene expression, metamerism)+Thermodynamics (metabolic rate scaling laws)] NESTED METABOLIC SCALES: Organisms evolve a fractal energy hierarchy—expensive fast-twitch micro-movements for local foraging (search radius <1 cell), moderate-cost medium bursts for patch migration (radius 5-10 cells), stable low-cost structures for shelter/storage (macroscopic body). Each scale operates independently but self-similar. Energy efficiency emerges because 90% of lifetime is spent in cheap micro-activity; beauty emerges from visible self-similar nesting (branching, dendritic patterns). Solves starvation by making search cheap at the scale where food is found (local clusters). — Math: Fractal dimension D: cost(search at scale s) ∝ s^D. Organisms evolve optimal D by distributing energy across scales. Total energy budget splits hierarchically: E_total = E_macro + E_meso + E_micro. Beauty measured as visual self-similarity index (correlation across scales). — Test: Plot energy expenditure vs. spatial scale (log-log). Real organisms show power-law relationships (Kleiber's law). If fractal foraging evolves, energy cost curve should show linear scaling, indicating fractal structure. Measure organism visual self-similarity (do branches at scale 1 resemble branches at scale 10?). Survival time should increase non-linearly with total energy budget.; [Biology (eusocial insects, symbiosis, Evo-Devo)+Physics (phase transitions, symmetry-breaking, network percolation)+Art (composition through contrast and diversity)] POLYMORPHIC CASTES WITH GROUP SELECTION: Stop selecting on individual organism fitness. Instead, organisms inherit a 'family gene' and group fitness is computed per family. Pressure shifts to DIVISION OF LABOR. Scout phenotype (small, fast, expensive) explores. Worker phenotype (medium, steady, cheap) collects. Storage phenotype (immobile, tiny metabolic cost) holds reserves. No caste can survive alone; all castes survive through cooperation. Beauty emerges from visual distinction (polymorphism = variety). Energy starvation disappears because scouts find food, workers process it, storage prevents loss. This reframes the fitness landscape entirely—it's no longer a peak-climbing problem, it's a cooperative network problem. — Math: Game theory: payoff matrix where solo organism gets fitness F_solo; caste member in family gets F_family × K (K is family size bonus). If F_family × K > F_solo for all castes, stable polymorphism emerges. Phase transition occurs at critical family size (percolation threshold). Beauty function: σ(phenotype_diversity) = -∑(pᵢ log pᵢ), entropy of phenotype distribution. — Test: Switch fitness function from individual to family-group for 50+ cycles. Track: (1) Do distinct morphs evolve? (2) What is family size distribution? (3) Do families out-compete solo organisms? (4) What is the critical family size where cooperation becomes stable? Predict phase transition around family size ~4-6 (seen in real eusocial insects). Measure visual beauty as morphotype count and distinctiveness.",
